geneVariantDescriptions.description: CDK8 amp indicates an increased number of copies of the CDK8 gene. However, the mechanism causing the increase is unspecified.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a clinical case study, combination Tafinlar (dabrafinib) and Mekinist (trametinib) therapy in a patient with Platinol (cisplatin)-resistant metastatic neuroendocrine carcinoma of the colon harboring BRAF V600E and TP53 H214R mutations and amplifications of FLT3 and CDK8 resulted in decreased disease burden with a clinical benefit for 5 months before disease progression (PMID: 30181415).

molecularProfile.profileName: BRAF V600E CDK8 amp FLT3 amp TP53 H214R

references.title: Targeting BRAF Mutations in High-Grade Neuroendocrine Carcinoma of the Colon.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a clinical case study, a patient with Platinol (cisplatin)-resistant metastatic neuroendocrine carcinoma of the colon harboring BRAF V600E and TP53 H214R mutations and amplifications of FLT3 and CDK8 who had an initial response to combination Tafinlar (dabrafinib) and Mekinist (trametinib) therapy was found to have acquired an ARID1B Q123* mutation upon disease progression (PMID: 30181415).
